Have you either ridden public transit much, or driven it?The current system is hard enough for a lot of people...I'm not entirely sure what problem you're trying to solve, but point to point public transit is *vastly* less efficient than the current "big busses on fixed routes" approach. Fraction of the passengers.I've driven both. As volume picked up, the door to door busses were nearly completely replaced by "big busses on fixed routes." The number of people carried went up, and generally we still got people where they wanted to go.
