Montreal doesn't even have bus-only lanes. I want that first.But we do have biodisel buses. And we do have a few routes that use smaller buses out of practicality. The issue with trying to optimize vehicle on certain routes size is you miss out on the randomness or accessibility for the disabled. It's a fairly safe assumption that buses will be more full at rush hour times, but there are always random times when a bus can be full. One of the longest routes here is almost always full no matter the time of day.
